  <main id="main">
    <section class="hero section-pad">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Discord storefronts</p>
          <h1>Sell from Discord without messy order tracking.</h1>
          <p class="hero-text">Store Bot gives your server a simple storefront for digital products, VIP perks, files, licenses, and services. Customers order from panels, staff manage the queue, and Premium can confirm payments from forwarded PayPal or Cash App emails.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Primary calls to action">
            <a class="button primary" href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1515919161690161224&permissions=2147483648&integration_type=0&scope=bot+applications.commands">Invite Store Bot</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href="https://discord.gg/zB7NgPBzBA">Join Support Server</a>
          </div>
          <a class="status-pill" id="homeStatusBadge" href="status.html" aria-label="View Store Bot live service status">
            <span class="status-pill-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span><strong>Status:</strong> <span id="homeStatusText">Checking...</span></span>
          </a>
          <div class="trust-row" aria-label="Store Bot highlights">
            <span>Free to start</span>
            <span>$1 first month</span>
            <span>$3/mo Premium</span>
            <span>Digital products</span>
            <span>Staff logs</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-panel reveal" aria-label="Example Store Bot panel">
          <div class="panel-top">
            <img src="assets/storebot-avatar.png" alt="Store Bot orange robot mascot" width="64" height="64" />
            <div>
              <strong>Example Server Store</strong>
              <span>Product panel preview</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-list">
            <div class="product-row"><span>VIP Access</span><strong>$5.00</strong></div>
            <div class="product-row"><span>Plugin Setup</span><strong>$15.00</strong></div>
            <div class="product-row"><span>License Key</span><strong>$10.00</strong></div>
          </div>
          <p class="panel-note">Demo only. Your products, prices, delivery text, and payment instructions are configured inside Discord.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="stats container reveal" aria-label="Store Bot quick facts">
      <div class="stat-card"><strong>10</strong><span>free product slots</span></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><strong>200</strong><span>premium product slots</span></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><strong>$3</strong><span>premium per month</span></div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-pad" id="features">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Core features</p>
          <h2>A practical store system for Discord servers.</h2>
          <p>Store Bot keeps the buying flow inside Discord while giving staff enough structure to avoid lost orders, unclear payment status, and scattered delivery notes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <article class="feature-card reveal"><span class="card-icon">01</span><h3>Store panels</h3><p>Post clean product panels where customers can start orders without digging through channels or DMs.</p></article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal"><span class="card-icon">02</span><h3>Order tracking</h3><p>Track pending, paid, delivered, cancelled, and completed orders with staff-friendly commands.</p></article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal"><span class="card-icon">03</span><h3>Digital delivery</h3><p>Use delivery text for licenses, files, codes, setup instructions, VIP perks, and service handoffs.</p></article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal"><span class="card-icon">04</span><h3>Staff controls</h3><p>Configure staff roles and log channels so the right people can manage products and customer orders.</p></article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal"><span class="card-icon">05</span><h3>Discounts and gift cards</h3><p>Premium stores can run promos, issue credit, and make returning customers easier to manage.</p></article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal"><span class="card-icon">06</span><h3>AutoPay forwarding</h3><p>Premium servers can forward PayPal or Cash App payment notification emails for automatic order matching.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-pad accent-section" id="autopay">
      <div class="container split-grid">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Premium AutoPay</p>
          <h2>Payment confirmation without handing over inbox access.</h2>
          <p class="section-text">Instead of asking every seller for IMAP settings, Store Bot can give premium servers forwarding instructions. Forward the payment notification email, and Store Bot checks the provider, order code, amount, currency, and status before marking a matching order paid.</p>
          <div class="check-list" role="list">
            <span role="listitem">Works with forwarded PayPal and Cash App payment notifications</span>
            <span role="listitem">Checks order code, amount, currency, provider, and status</span>
            <span role="listitem">Only matches active pending orders</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <article class="notice-card reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Important</p>
          <h3>Store Bot is not a payment processor.</h3>
          <p>Payments still happen through the seller's chosen payment method. AutoPay helps match payment notification emails to Store Bot orders so staff do not have to mark every order manually.</p>
          <a class="inline-link" href="autopay.html">Read AutoPay details →</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Store Bot Shop Reputation Section: start -->
<section class="section-pad trust-showcase-section" id="shop-reputation">
 <div class="container split-grid">
  <div class="reveal">
   <p class="eyebrow">New seller tools</p>
   <h2>Public shop pages and seller reputation for Discord stores.</h2>
   <p class="section-text">Store Bot is built for sellers who need more than a Discord channel full of product posts. Shop Pages and Reputation Pages help sellers show products, policies, completed order signals, and verified reviews in one public place.</p>
   <div class="hero-actions">
    <a class="button primary" href="shop.html">Explore Shop Pages</a>
    <a class="button secondary" href="reputation.html">View Reputation Tools</a>
   </div>
  </div>
  <article class="trust-showcase-card reveal" aria-label="Example seller trust profile">
   <span class="verified-badge">Verified Store Bot seller</span>
   <h3>Example Seller Profile</h3>
   <p>Display products, Discord invite, payment instructions, support policy, and verified order reviews from one page.</p>
   <div class="seller-metrics">
    <span><strong>4.9★</strong> rating</span>
    <span><strong>128</strong> orders</span>
    <span><strong>0</strong> active disputes</span>
   </div>
   <div class="review-stack">
    <blockquote>“Fast delivery and easy checkout.” <span>Verified order</span></blockquote>
   </div>
   <p class="panel-note">Example only. Real seller pages can connect to Store Bot order and review data as the feature grows.</p>
  </article>
 </div>
</section>
<!-- Store Bot Shop Reputation Section: end -->
<section class="section-pad" id="pricing">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
          <h2>Start free. Upgrade when the store is active.</h2>
          <p>The free plan is enough to test your store. Premium is $3/month, with a $1 first month for first-time users, and adds the tools that matter once people are actually buying.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-grid">
          <article class="price-card reveal">
            <div><h3>Free</h3><p>For testing or small stores.</p></div>
            <div class="price">$0</div>
            <ul>
              <li>Up to 10 products</li>
              <li>Product panels</li>
              <li>Manual payment handling</li>
              <li>Manual delivery tools</li>
              <li>Store Bot branding</li>
            </ul>
            <a class="button secondary full" href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1515919161690161224&permissions=2147483648&integration_type=0&scope=bot+applications.commands">Invite Free</a>
          </article>
          <article class="price-card premium reveal">
            <div class="badge">Premium</div>
            <div><h3>Premium</h3><p>For active Discord stores.</p></div>
            <div class="price">$3<span>/mo</span></div>
            <p class="price-note">First month is $1 for first-time users.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Up to 200 products</li>
              <li>No forced upgrade ads</li>
              <li>AutoPay email forwarding</li>
              <li>Discount codes and gift cards</li>
              <li>Custom branding, staff roles, and logs</li>
            </ul>
            <a class="button primary full" href="https://discord.gg/zB7NgPBzBA">Upgrade in Discord</a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="setup" class="section-pad setup-section" id="setup">
      <div class="container split-grid">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Setup</p>
          <h2>From invite to live panel in a few steps.</h2>
          <p class="section-text">The setup is designed around commands a server owner or trusted staff member can run inside Discord.</p>
        </div>
        <ol class="steps reveal">
          <li><strong>Invite Store Bot</strong><span>Add the bot with slash command access.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Run <code>/storebot setup</code></strong><span>Set your store title, support channel, and payment instructions.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Add products</strong><span>Create products with prices, descriptions, and delivery text.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Set staff and logs</strong><span>Choose staff roles and the channel used for order updates.</span></li>
          <li><strong>Post the panel</strong><span>Publish the storefront panel where customers can start orders.</span></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-pad" id="use-cases">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Use cases</p>
          <h2>Made for Discord communities that sell digital access.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-grid">
          <article class="mini-card reveal"><h3>Gaming communities</h3><p>VIP access, server perks, private roles, CS2 community items, and setup services.</p></article>
          <article class="mini-card reveal"><h3>Software sellers</h3><p>License keys, serial keys, config files, ZIP downloads, and support packages.</p></article>
          <article class="mini-card reveal"><h3>Service providers</h3><p>Custom Discord work, plugin installs, design work, and order queues that need staff visibility.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="faq" class="section-pad faq-section" id="faq">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
          <h2>Quick answers before you install.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <details class="faq-card reveal"><summary>What can I sell with Store Bot?</summary><p>Digital products, VIP access, license keys, serial keys, configs, setup services, game server perks, and similar Discord-based products.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-card reveal"><summary>Does Store Bot process payments?</summary><p>No. Store Bot does not hold funds or process cards. Sellers configure their own payment instructions and can use Premium AutoPay forwarding to help confirm matching payments.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-card reveal"><summary>Do I have to enter IMAP settings?</summary><p>No. Forwarding AutoPay lets premium server owners forward payment notification emails instead of giving the bot direct inbox access.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-card reveal"><summary>Can staff manage orders?</summary><p>Yes. Server owners can configure staff roles and logs so trusted members can help manage the store.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-card reveal"><summary>Is the homepage preview real?</summary><p>No. It is a demo showing the layout. Your server controls the product names, prices, and delivery text.</p></details>
          <details class="faq-card reveal"><summary>Where do I get support?</summary><p>Join the support server and open a ticket or ask for help there.</p></details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-pad cta-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cta-card reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Ready</p>
          <h2>Set up your Discord store with Store Bot.</h2>
          <p>Invite the bot, add products, publish a panel, and keep orders organized from the start.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions center">
            <a class="button primary" href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1515919161690161224&permissions=2147483648&integration_type=0&scope=bot+applications.commands">Invite Store Bot</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href="https://discord.gg/zB7NgPBzBA">Get Support</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
